1
00:00:43,043 --> 00:00:46,630
CHAPTER 42:
WHY ONLY HER?

2
00:00:47,548 --> 00:00:49,967
What will happen if Mr. Ga finds out?

3
00:00:50,968 --> 00:00:53,846
Do you think you'll still
be able to talk to him like that?

4
00:00:54,764 --> 00:00:55,806
Drink this and cheer up.

5
00:00:59,101 --> 00:01:00,227
Just you wait and see, Eui-ju.

6
00:01:01,353 --> 00:01:02,563
You're done for.

7
00:01:04,982 --> 00:01:06,734
COUNSELING ROOM

8
00:01:06,817 --> 00:01:08,068
COUNSELING IN PROGRESS

9
00:01:12,156 --> 00:01:13,741
What is it you want to tell me?

10
00:01:14,575 --> 00:01:16,494
I've given this a lot of thought.

11
00:01:17,244 --> 00:01:19,038
I thought you should know, Mr. Ga.

12
00:01:21,123 --> 00:01:22,458
One of the girls in our class

13
00:01:23,042 --> 00:01:24,960
has written a novel about you.

14
00:01:26,128 --> 00:01:27,379
And a BL novel at that.

15
00:01:28,964 --> 00:01:30,674
Everyone's talking about it online.

16
00:01:32,676 --> 00:01:34,261
Do you know who wrote it?

17
00:01:37,431 --> 00:01:38,682
It was Eui-ju.

18
00:01:44,563 --> 00:01:45,856
I said it was Eui-ju.

19
00:01:49,902 --> 00:01:51,153
I know.

20
00:01:53,697 --> 00:01:55,199
You already knew?

21
00:01:56,158 --> 00:01:57,284
How…

22
00:01:59,286 --> 00:02:01,705
Why aren't you upset?
Doesn't it bother you?

23
00:02:02,498 --> 00:02:05,251
I think Eui-ju is creepy
and kind of scary.

24
00:02:06,544 --> 00:02:08,587
You need to read it for yourself.

25
00:02:16,095 --> 00:02:17,096
Wait…

26
00:02:18,138 --> 00:02:19,390
Have you already read it?

27
00:02:24,019 --> 00:02:26,021
But you haven't done anything about it?
Why not?

28
00:02:27,147 --> 00:02:28,524
Why, Mr. Ga?

29
00:02:29,525 --> 00:02:31,318
Why do you give her special treatment?

30
00:02:33,404 --> 00:02:34,238
What do you mean?

31
00:02:34,321 --> 00:02:37,032
Why do you only look out for her
and take special care of her?

32
00:02:39,201 --> 00:02:40,870
Why waste your energy
on someone like Eui-ju?

33
00:02:41,871 --> 00:02:43,747
It's not just this novel,
but after-school math too.

34
00:02:43,831 --> 00:02:44,832
Why only her?

35
00:02:46,876 --> 00:02:48,085
Mr. Ga,

36
00:02:48,669 --> 00:02:51,046
you don't really need to
look out for someone like her.

37
00:02:52,381 --> 00:02:54,258
I think you're misunderstanding something.

38
00:02:55,384 --> 00:02:57,052
I'm not doing this because it's Eui-ju.

39
00:02:58,637 --> 00:03:00,222
I would have done the same for you.

40
00:03:00,973 --> 00:03:03,058
Don't give me that.

41
00:03:03,809 --> 00:03:04,810
What I mean is,

42
00:03:04,894 --> 00:03:08,188
shouldn't you be looking out for me
rather than someone like her?

43
00:03:08,981 --> 00:03:10,441
I'm Eun Ha-su.

44
00:03:10,524 --> 00:03:11,901
I'm the Eun Ha-su!

45
00:03:35,007 --> 00:03:36,467
You're both screwed now.

46
00:03:42,431 --> 00:03:45,809
CHAPTER 43:
WHO IS IMUK?

47
00:03:51,732 --> 00:03:54,568
CHECK THIS OUT
THIS IS ABOUT OUR TEACHERS?

48
00:04:07,164 --> 00:04:08,749
Guys, check out this web novel.

49
00:04:08,832 --> 00:04:10,501
The story is about our teachers,

50
00:04:10,584 --> 00:04:12,586
and apparently,
the writer goes to our school.

51
00:04:18,884 --> 00:04:20,427
-Freaking wild, isn't it?
-Our teachers?

52
00:04:20,511 --> 00:04:21,929
-It's about our school.
-Really?

53
00:04:22,763 --> 00:04:24,473
Isn't this Mr. Ga?

54
00:04:25,849 --> 00:04:27,101
WE WERE FRIENDS

55
00:04:27,685 --> 00:04:29,395
Hey, have you seen this?

56
00:04:30,104 --> 00:04:31,772
This is about our teachers, right?

57
00:04:31,855 --> 00:04:33,607
It's crazy.

58
00:04:33,691 --> 00:04:36,360
Go on. Check it out already.

59
00:04:45,369 --> 00:04:46,620
Why are the letters so small?

60
00:04:46,704 --> 00:04:47,579
EPISODE 14

61
00:04:47,663 --> 00:04:49,123
So what's all this?

62
00:04:49,748 --> 00:04:50,791
It's a BL novel

63
00:04:50,874 --> 00:04:52,710
featuring men in a same-sex relationship.

64
00:04:52,793 --> 00:04:54,628
Our new teachers are the main characters.

65
00:04:55,129 --> 00:04:58,465
You'll see that the teachers
are portrayed as liking each other.

66
00:04:58,549 --> 00:05:00,467
Mr. Ga and Mr. Jung

67
00:05:00,551 --> 00:05:02,636
are in a love triangle with Mr. Yoon.

68
00:05:03,679 --> 00:05:06,223
Enough. What did I just hear?

69
00:05:06,932 --> 00:05:08,684
I can't say I understand
what you're saying.

70
00:05:08,767 --> 00:05:09,768
Oh, I feel dizzy.

71
00:05:09,852 --> 00:05:10,978
This is clearly defamation

72
00:05:11,061 --> 00:05:13,188
and a violation
of their professional rights.

73
00:05:14,189 --> 00:05:17,735
If this goes up on an online community
with enough traffic,

74
00:05:18,944 --> 00:05:20,237
it'll probably make the news.

75
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:23,032
But I really don't want our school

76
00:05:23,115 --> 00:05:25,951
to get caught up in something so shameful.

77
00:05:27,911 --> 00:05:29,788
Of course not.

78
00:05:29,872 --> 00:05:31,707
We have to keep things
as quiet as possible

79
00:05:31,790 --> 00:05:33,292
and resolve things internally.

80
00:05:33,375 --> 00:05:34,960
Oh, my head.

81
00:05:35,044 --> 00:05:37,087
There's never a quiet day
in this damn place.

82
00:05:39,757 --> 00:05:43,510
Don't worry, I'll take care of it.
You can leave, Ha-su.

83
00:05:51,018 --> 00:05:52,144
What in the…

84
00:06:15,167 --> 00:06:16,376
It's you, isn't it?

85
00:06:17,294 --> 00:06:19,296
Is it really you?
Did you write that novel?

86
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:21,632
Did you really write it
based on our teachers?

87
00:06:24,593 --> 00:06:25,511
Yeah.

88
00:06:27,096 --> 00:06:28,347
This is insane.

89
00:06:30,891 --> 00:06:33,477
-The thing is, Go-ya--
-Is that why you've been so out of it?

90
00:06:35,312 --> 00:06:37,940
Why didn't you say anything?
You must have felt so alone.

91
00:06:45,531 --> 00:06:47,699
Did you think I wouldn't understand?

92
00:06:48,951 --> 00:06:50,494
It's not that, Go-ya.

93
00:06:50,577 --> 00:06:52,204
It wasn't like that.

94
00:06:52,287 --> 00:06:54,414
It's not that I didn't trust you.

95
00:06:54,498 --> 00:06:55,415
I was…

96
00:06:58,794 --> 00:07:00,462
I guess I was embarrassed.

97
00:07:03,882 --> 00:07:05,384
I was ashamed.

98
00:07:08,178 --> 00:07:10,514
When I checked it out,
the views were out of this world.

99
00:07:11,098 --> 00:07:13,183
You said I'd be the first to know
when you hit the big time.

100
00:07:16,436 --> 00:07:17,604
I'm sorry.

101
00:07:20,816 --> 00:07:22,317
So what gave you away?

102
00:07:23,026 --> 00:07:24,903
How did Ha-su catch on to you?

103
00:07:27,447 --> 00:07:29,366
I'm not really sure.

104
00:07:30,033 --> 00:07:31,994
I got the feeling she'd figured it out

105
00:07:32,077 --> 00:07:33,412
a few days ago.

106
00:07:35,831 --> 00:07:38,709
My gosh, Eui-ju.

107
00:07:39,293 --> 00:07:40,961
Writing about our teachers?

108
00:07:41,044 --> 00:07:42,838
You're something else.

109
00:07:43,630 --> 00:07:44,715
It'll be fine.

110
00:07:45,299 --> 00:07:46,133
Let's go.

111
00:07:49,887 --> 00:07:51,388
"If you don't want to
solve these problems,

112
00:07:51,471 --> 00:07:52,806
you can do something else."

113
00:07:52,890 --> 00:07:54,016
Damn!

114
00:07:56,185 --> 00:07:58,770
Did you check out the comments?

115
00:08:03,192 --> 00:08:04,985
-Hey.
-Hey, Ha-su.

116
00:08:05,068 --> 00:08:07,196
How do you know Eui-ju is Imuk?
Have you got proof?

117
00:08:07,279 --> 00:08:08,447
Well, do you?

118
00:08:08,530 --> 00:08:11,325
Mr. Ga's comments from after-school math
are there word-for-word.

119
00:08:13,035 --> 00:08:14,244
I know you can see it too.

120
00:08:14,328 --> 00:08:17,039
It also contains things he said
in his very first homeroom.

121
00:08:18,207 --> 00:08:20,792
Let's be frank here.
Is that really such a heinous crime?

122
00:08:20,876 --> 00:08:22,044
So what if she is?

123
00:08:23,128 --> 00:08:24,338
Don't you think

124
00:08:24,963 --> 00:08:26,548
kids like that are a bit weird?

125
00:08:26,632 --> 00:08:28,258
Jeez. How creepy.

126
00:08:29,176 --> 00:08:31,345
Hey, everyone has different tastes.

127
00:08:31,428 --> 00:08:33,680
Just mind your own business.

128
00:08:33,764 --> 00:08:36,808
Even so, how can she write
about our teachers like that?

129
00:08:37,601 --> 00:08:41,271
Imagine if she writes about us
like that behind our backs?

130
00:08:41,355 --> 00:08:43,106
She might even be writing right now.

131
00:08:43,190 --> 00:08:44,441
Some lesbian crap about our school.

132
00:08:45,400 --> 00:08:46,610
That's so freaky.

133
00:08:46,693 --> 00:08:49,112
Freaks like her would insist
it's a matter of freedom of speech

134
00:08:49,196 --> 00:08:50,697
but then go on to become criminals.

135
00:08:51,281 --> 00:08:52,115
Hey, you…

136
00:08:56,495 --> 00:08:57,829
I guess we can ask her directly.

137
00:08:59,831 --> 00:09:01,875
-There you are, Eui-ju.
-Hey, Eui-ju.

138
00:09:01,959 --> 00:09:02,793
Morning.

139
00:09:03,835 --> 00:09:05,087
-Good morning.
-Yeah.

140
00:09:08,757 --> 00:09:12,010
If the disciplinary committee is involved,
your parents will be told.

141
00:09:12,886 --> 00:09:14,721
If my parents ever read
the BL novel I wrote,

142
00:09:15,639 --> 00:09:17,266
I'm running away pronto.

143
00:09:17,349 --> 00:09:18,934
-True that.
-For sure.

144
00:09:19,017 --> 00:09:20,894
I'd want to disappear
off the face of the earth.

145
00:09:20,978 --> 00:09:22,646
-Fair enough.
-It's that bad.

146
00:09:23,397 --> 00:09:24,940
Damn it, you crazy bitch!

147
00:09:35,158 --> 00:09:36,118
-Stop it!
-Hey!

148
00:09:37,953 --> 00:09:39,204
What's going on here?

149
00:10:08,191 --> 00:10:09,067
Eui-ju,

150
00:10:10,610 --> 00:10:11,445
come with me.

151
00:10:20,996 --> 00:10:21,997
-Hey.
-What?

152
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:23,999
-What are you doing?
-Stop it.

153
00:10:24,082 --> 00:10:25,584
-Stop it!
-Hey!

154
00:10:25,667 --> 00:10:26,877
-Why, you…
-Stop it, will you?

155
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:32,132
CHAPTER 44: YOU MUST TAKE RESPONSIBILITY
FOR YOUR ACTIONS

156
00:10:49,232 --> 00:10:50,067
Mr. Ga.

157
00:10:52,194 --> 00:10:54,404
Just pretend you didn't know.

158
00:10:57,199 --> 00:10:59,951
I don't want you getting in trouble
because of me.

159
00:11:03,538 --> 00:11:06,249
Shouldn't you be worrying about yourself?

160
00:11:06,958 --> 00:11:09,544
It's only right
that I take responsibility.

161
00:11:11,046 --> 00:11:12,589
So, you can

162
00:11:12,672 --> 00:11:13,673
just…

163
00:11:14,508 --> 00:11:15,717
say you didn't know.

164
00:11:17,302 --> 00:11:18,553
Okay?

165
00:11:18,637 --> 00:11:20,097
You have to.

166
00:11:20,180 --> 00:11:23,183
We'll say you didn't know anything,
just like the other teachers.

167
00:11:24,017 --> 00:11:26,603
This was all my own doing.

168
00:11:27,938 --> 00:11:28,897
So,

169
00:11:30,065 --> 00:11:33,151
it has nothing to do with you, sir.

170
00:11:38,532 --> 00:11:40,409
You'll have to face
the disciplinary committee.

171
00:11:41,618 --> 00:11:44,996
Think about what you're going to say
and how you'll take responsibility,

172
00:11:45,872 --> 00:11:47,040
and prepare well.

173
00:11:50,252 --> 00:11:51,420
Yes, sir.

174
00:11:53,422 --> 00:11:54,756
I will take responsibility too.

175
00:11:56,216 --> 00:11:58,385
I'm partly responsible, for sure.

176
00:11:59,928 --> 00:12:02,848
But you'll have to take responsibility
for your part. That's unavoidable.

177
00:12:05,976 --> 00:12:08,019
Yes, sir. I know.

178
00:12:09,563 --> 00:12:10,772
I'm sure you're scared.

179
00:12:11,731 --> 00:12:13,608
You're probably full of regret
and embarrassed too.

180
00:12:14,109 --> 00:12:15,777
It might feel like
everything is crumbling down.

181
00:12:17,070 --> 00:12:19,072
But this doesn't mean your life is over.

182
00:12:20,407 --> 00:12:22,534
It might feel like that right now,

183
00:12:23,368 --> 00:12:24,703
but it's not.

184
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:31,835
I don't know how things will turn out.

185
00:12:32,544 --> 00:12:34,337
But what matters more than the results,

186
00:12:34,421 --> 00:12:37,382
is how you comport yourself
during the process, accept it,

187
00:12:38,091 --> 00:12:39,342
and deal with it.

188
00:12:40,552 --> 00:12:41,970
Do you get what I'm saying?

189
00:12:44,473 --> 00:12:45,515
Yes, sir.

190
00:12:51,396 --> 00:12:53,440
The principal wants to see you. Let's go.

191
00:12:59,404 --> 00:13:00,530
What is this?

192
00:13:01,156 --> 00:13:03,158
What on earth is this? The teachers…

193
00:13:05,202 --> 00:13:07,496
How dare you make your teachers
characters in a novel?

194
00:13:07,579 --> 00:13:09,164
You. A student!

195
00:13:09,748 --> 00:13:12,375
This is unacceptable.

196
00:13:12,459 --> 00:13:14,377
Ms. Kim, the thing is…

197
00:13:15,378 --> 00:13:17,672
What do you take this school for?
And your teachers?

198
00:13:17,756 --> 00:13:19,299
How dare you? You, a student!

199
00:13:19,382 --> 00:13:21,551
A student mocking teachers
and turning them into a joke…

200
00:13:21,635 --> 00:13:23,803
Is this what education has become?

201
00:13:25,013 --> 00:13:27,516
What on earth
are the kids of today learning?

202
00:13:27,599 --> 00:13:29,809
Making fools out of their teachers.

203
00:13:31,269 --> 00:13:32,812
Delete it immediately!

204
00:13:32,896 --> 00:13:34,564
Wipe it from the Internet.

205
00:13:34,648 --> 00:13:36,983
What will happen to the school's
reputation if parents find out?

206
00:13:38,235 --> 00:13:41,446
It's an absolute disgrace.

207
00:13:42,155 --> 00:13:43,532
I'm sorry.

208
00:13:44,658 --> 00:13:47,452
Ms. Kim, may I add something? Actually--

209
00:13:47,536 --> 00:13:50,038
If you have something to say,
save it for the hearing.

210
00:13:50,121 --> 00:13:52,332
Make sure Eui-ju's parents attend.

211
00:13:52,415 --> 00:13:53,542
And the other teachers too.

212
00:13:53,625 --> 00:13:55,794
The ones in the novel.

213
00:13:55,877 --> 00:13:58,463
Mr. Yoon, Mr. Jung, and Mr. Noh.

214
00:14:03,677 --> 00:14:04,803
Yes, ma'am.

215
00:14:06,680 --> 00:14:08,098
I'll see that she's expelled.

216
00:14:08,181 --> 00:14:10,559
This is completely unacceptable!

217
00:14:16,481 --> 00:14:18,108
MALE TEACHERS' LOUNGE

218
00:14:31,830 --> 00:14:32,872
What is this?

219
00:14:35,834 --> 00:14:38,545
Wow, your reading comprehension
is really something else.

220
00:14:40,338 --> 00:14:42,257
Listen carefully.

221
00:14:44,092 --> 00:14:45,385
You and him,

222
00:14:46,052 --> 00:14:47,721
and him and Woo-su

223
00:14:48,305 --> 00:14:50,473
are involved-involved.
Let me put it this way.

224
00:14:50,557 --> 00:14:53,184
That kid let her imagination
run dangerously wild

225
00:14:53,268 --> 00:14:55,395
and came up with a delusional fiction.

226
00:14:55,478 --> 00:14:57,147
Why were we paired up anyway?

227
00:15:00,942 --> 00:15:02,861
Just forget it.

228
00:15:03,737 --> 00:15:04,571
But…

229
00:15:05,864 --> 00:15:07,324
Letter girl, that brat!

230
00:15:07,407 --> 00:15:09,909
What did I tell you
about that weird glint in her eyes?

231
00:15:09,993 --> 00:15:11,745
I'm a great judge of character, you know.

232
00:15:14,831 --> 00:15:17,334
How long are you going
to keep reading that?

233
00:15:17,417 --> 00:15:20,879
So, is this a matter
of freedom of expression

234
00:15:20,962 --> 00:15:22,297
or invasion of privacy?

235
00:15:23,673 --> 00:15:24,924
Should we do something?

236
00:15:25,008 --> 00:15:26,801
Is this something we should sue over?

237
00:15:27,427 --> 00:15:28,720
Okay, shall I call a lawyer?

238
00:15:28,803 --> 00:15:31,139
What should we sue her for?

239
00:15:31,222 --> 00:15:32,599
Defamation.

240
00:15:32,682 --> 00:15:34,559
Hey, kids are gonna mess around.

241
00:15:34,643 --> 00:15:35,727
Man, this guy's trouble.

242
00:15:35,810 --> 00:15:37,187
That's a dangerous take.

243
00:15:37,854 --> 00:15:39,648
This isn't something
we should just let go.

244
00:15:39,731 --> 00:15:40,857
See.

245
00:15:40,940 --> 00:15:41,775
No?

246
00:15:41,858 --> 00:15:44,486
She quoted us verbatim
without our permission.

247
00:15:44,986 --> 00:15:46,905
The things we said and did.

248
00:15:47,530 --> 00:15:49,366
Since she didn't ask our permission,

249
00:15:49,449 --> 00:15:51,618
if we've suffered any damages,

250
00:15:51,701 --> 00:15:53,036
we can sue her in civil court.

251
00:15:53,119 --> 00:15:54,204
Yeah.

252
00:15:54,913 --> 00:15:58,667
There's no clear rule about the boundary
between real life and fiction,

253
00:15:59,501 --> 00:16:01,336
but questions will arise
on the author's ethics.

254
00:16:02,045 --> 00:16:02,879
Wow.

255
00:16:03,713 --> 00:16:06,299
See? By the way, why are you being

256
00:16:06,383 --> 00:16:07,884
a fierce tiger baring its teeth,

257
00:16:07,967 --> 00:16:11,554
instead of the cuddly pussycat
you normally are?

258
00:16:12,555 --> 00:16:13,723
However,

259
00:16:15,225 --> 00:16:17,477
if we acknowledge
we haven't suffered any harm,

260
00:16:17,560 --> 00:16:19,062
then there's no real issue.

261
00:16:19,896 --> 00:16:21,481
So basically,

262
00:16:22,440 --> 00:16:24,317
Eui-ju's punishment hinges on what we say?

263
00:16:24,401 --> 00:16:25,276
Yeah.

264
00:16:33,201 --> 00:16:34,452
What did the principal say?

265
00:16:35,078 --> 00:16:36,329
She's going crazy, right?

266
00:16:37,747 --> 00:16:38,790
There'll be a hearing.

267
00:16:39,958 --> 00:16:41,126
She wants you guys to attend.

268
00:16:43,336 --> 00:16:47,090
According to Dong-ju, the published author
with a degree in Korean Education,

269
00:16:47,173 --> 00:16:48,758
our opinion on the matter

270
00:16:48,842 --> 00:16:51,803
would affect the punishment
for that little brat, Eui-ju.

271
00:16:51,886 --> 00:16:52,887
What are you going to do?

272
00:16:56,266 --> 00:16:58,143
How should she be punished?

273
00:17:00,019 --> 00:17:04,566
Woo-su, use that brilliant mind of yours
to come up with a cruel punishment.

274
00:17:04,649 --> 00:17:06,568
-Hey.
-What?

275
00:17:09,654 --> 00:17:11,156
We should each make our own decision.

276
00:17:23,042 --> 00:17:24,127
Are you okay?

277
00:17:28,506 --> 00:17:29,758
Don't worry about the others.

278
00:17:30,425 --> 00:17:32,302
It'll all blow over in a week or so.

279
00:18:04,375 --> 00:18:05,376
Oh, Dad.

280
00:18:05,460 --> 00:18:08,213
Hey, baby. Fancy seeing you here.

281
00:18:09,088 --> 00:18:10,173
There's no need.

282
00:18:11,216 --> 00:18:13,635
Why do you look so down? Are you sick?

283
00:18:14,344 --> 00:18:15,887
No, it's just that

284
00:18:16,554 --> 00:18:17,889
I'm a bit tired.

285
00:18:18,890 --> 00:18:21,726
Are you okay?
You've been doing a lot of overtime.

286
00:18:21,810 --> 00:18:22,769
True.

287
00:18:22,852 --> 00:18:24,687
Drawing up the budget.

288
00:18:25,355 --> 00:18:27,315
Dealing with residents' complaints.

289
00:18:27,398 --> 00:18:28,483
My goodness.

290
00:18:29,734 --> 00:18:32,779
But as soon as I see your face,

291
00:18:32,862 --> 00:18:35,198
all the stress melts away.

292
00:18:35,281 --> 00:18:36,950
Away it goes.

293
00:18:43,206 --> 00:18:44,582
Is it because of all the studying?

294
00:18:45,250 --> 00:18:46,543
Shall I buy you an ice cream?

295
00:18:46,626 --> 00:18:48,086
No, I'm okay.

296
00:18:56,511 --> 00:18:57,345
Kid.

297
00:18:59,347 --> 00:19:00,723
Let me give you some dad wisdom.

298
00:19:01,349 --> 00:19:03,268
After living a fair few years now,

299
00:19:04,269 --> 00:19:06,563
I realized that life

300
00:19:06,646 --> 00:19:10,650
is about carrying a lot of worries
with you wherever you go.

301
00:19:11,818 --> 00:19:13,987
I guess that's to be expected.

302
00:19:15,071 --> 00:19:16,447
So whatever happens in your life,

303
00:19:17,615 --> 00:19:18,950
don't worry too much.

304
00:19:22,620 --> 00:19:23,621
Okay.

305
00:19:25,790 --> 00:19:28,084
I don't know
what you're worrying about these days,

306
00:19:29,168 --> 00:19:32,130
but it probably feels like
the biggest thing in the world.

307
00:19:32,881 --> 00:19:34,591
And of course, that's understandable.

308
00:19:34,674 --> 00:19:35,925
When I was your age,

309
00:19:36,801 --> 00:19:40,054
I felt like the world
was collapsing around me every day.

310
00:19:41,055 --> 00:19:43,725
But looking back,

311
00:19:44,350 --> 00:19:47,687
all those things
I bawled my eyes out over…

312
00:19:48,438 --> 00:19:50,982
Turned out to be nothing?

313
00:19:51,608 --> 00:19:53,026
No.

314
00:19:53,109 --> 00:19:55,820
I'd be lying if I said they were nothing.

315
00:19:56,738 --> 00:19:58,948
But looking back,

316
00:20:00,617 --> 00:20:01,868
like pieces of armor,

317
00:20:02,493 --> 00:20:05,788
they stuck to me here and there

318
00:20:06,789 --> 00:20:09,000
and made me stronger.

319
00:20:10,710 --> 00:20:11,669
So, Eui-ju,

320
00:20:12,754 --> 00:20:15,423
just go at your own pace.

321
00:20:16,507 --> 00:20:19,469
Don't rush or push yourself too hard.

322
00:20:20,136 --> 00:20:22,263
Rest when you need to.

323
00:20:23,222 --> 00:20:25,141
I'll stay right by your side

324
00:20:25,683 --> 00:20:27,143
so that when you're tired,

325
00:20:27,226 --> 00:20:30,688
I can bring you
a nice cold glass of water.

326
00:20:35,276 --> 00:20:36,694
Even if things are rough now,

327
00:20:37,487 --> 00:20:38,988
they will work out in the end.

328
00:20:39,906 --> 00:20:40,782
Honestly, they will.

329
00:20:41,658 --> 00:20:44,035
I've seen it for myself.

330
00:20:50,792 --> 00:20:51,918
Dad, I…

331
00:20:53,503 --> 00:20:54,504
To tell the truth,

332
00:20:55,296 --> 00:20:57,090
there's something I need to tell you.

333
00:21:02,512 --> 00:21:03,680
CHAPTER 45:
HELLO, THIS IS IMUK

334
00:21:03,763 --> 00:21:04,806
What does she want to say?

335
00:21:05,348 --> 00:21:07,475
I don't know. Let's wait and see.

336
00:21:22,407 --> 00:21:23,825
Why are you doing that?

337
00:21:24,450 --> 00:21:25,702
What's this?

338
00:21:25,785 --> 00:21:27,787
If you stay like that,
you'll hurt your knees.

339
00:21:27,870 --> 00:21:28,705
Get up.

340
00:21:28,788 --> 00:21:30,665
Mom, Dad. I write novels online.

341
00:21:33,418 --> 00:21:34,335
Novels?

342
00:21:36,421 --> 00:21:37,797
I was in eighth grade

343
00:21:38,923 --> 00:21:39,841
when I first started.

344
00:21:43,219 --> 00:21:44,554
Nobody ever reads them.

345
00:21:46,097 --> 00:21:47,473
But I enjoyed it.

346
00:21:50,143 --> 00:21:51,436
Writing novels

347
00:21:51,519 --> 00:21:54,105
and seeing the characters
I created come to life

348
00:21:54,731 --> 00:21:55,940
was so exciting.

349
00:21:57,108 --> 00:21:59,694
So I kept writing.

350
00:22:00,987 --> 00:22:03,906
Even when I didn't want to get up
in the morning or go to school,

351
00:22:03,990 --> 00:22:06,617
just thinking about writing at night
gave me such a thrill.

352
00:22:07,827 --> 00:22:08,661
I…

353
00:22:10,747 --> 00:22:13,458
I know I'm not much good at anything.

354
00:22:14,876 --> 00:22:16,627
And what's more,

355
00:22:17,295 --> 00:22:18,796
I never particularly enjoyed anything.

356
00:22:19,964 --> 00:22:21,549
But for the first time ever,

357
00:22:23,217 --> 00:22:24,886
I found something I really enjoyed.

358
00:22:26,763 --> 00:22:27,680
And that was…

359
00:22:29,390 --> 00:22:30,725
writing novels.

360
00:22:33,227 --> 00:22:35,104
Writing novels of all things.

361
00:22:37,982 --> 00:22:39,525
I wonder who you take after.

362
00:22:41,152 --> 00:22:41,986
So,

363
00:22:43,029 --> 00:22:44,280
what's the problem?

364
00:22:45,615 --> 00:22:47,742
My latest work

365
00:22:47,825 --> 00:22:50,244
was really popular.

366
00:22:50,328 --> 00:22:52,830
It got a huge number of views and likes.

367
00:22:52,914 --> 00:22:56,375
And a famous publisher
agreed to launch it.

368
00:22:56,959 --> 00:22:58,377
That's amazing.

369
00:22:58,461 --> 00:23:00,671
I'm so proud of you, my girl!

370
00:23:00,755 --> 00:23:01,798
But the thing is…

371
00:23:03,966 --> 00:23:06,928
the story was all about my teachers.

372
00:23:12,725 --> 00:23:13,976
I based my main characters

373
00:23:15,436 --> 00:23:18,523
on my teachers.

374
00:23:20,316 --> 00:23:22,401
People at school found out.

375
00:23:24,779 --> 00:23:27,156
And now the principal
wants to hold a disciplinary hearing.

376
00:23:27,240 --> 00:23:28,074
What?

377
00:23:29,117 --> 00:23:30,952
This is my novel.

378
00:23:31,702 --> 00:23:33,955
I'm sorry.
Wait until I'm in my room to read it.

379
00:23:42,338 --> 00:23:45,341
Why hold a disciplinary hearing
over a novel?

380
00:23:46,342 --> 00:23:48,010
MURIM GIRLS' HIGH SCHOOL

381
00:24:01,649 --> 00:24:07,071
WE WERE FRIENDS
HELLO, THIS IS IMUK

382
00:24:11,492 --> 00:24:14,954
Hello, this is Imuk.

383
00:24:16,122 --> 00:24:19,667
I wrote We Were Friends using traits

384
00:24:19,750 --> 00:24:21,586
of real people around me as inspiration.

385
00:24:22,670 --> 00:24:26,215
I dissected aspects of their daily life,
their way of speaking, and their habits,

386
00:24:26,299 --> 00:24:30,636
and arbitrarily adapted them for my story.

387
00:24:31,762 --> 00:24:33,222
As a writer,

388
00:24:33,973 --> 00:24:36,017
I should've created something of my own,

389
00:24:36,100 --> 00:24:37,435
but I couldn't.

390
00:24:39,145 --> 00:24:41,063
I sincerely apologize.

391
00:24:42,273 --> 00:24:45,985
I've only now realized
that my writing caused discomfort

392
00:24:46,068 --> 00:24:49,280
and hurt to others.

393
00:24:50,781 --> 00:24:53,701
I sincerely apologize.

394
00:24:57,121 --> 00:25:00,541
Writing this story made me very happy.

395
00:25:00,625 --> 00:25:02,126
I felt excited.

396
00:25:03,044 --> 00:25:06,964
But that happiness was built
by borrowing from others,

397
00:25:07,048 --> 00:25:08,925
no, by taking from them

398
00:25:09,008 --> 00:25:11,177
without their permission.

399
00:25:11,260 --> 00:25:13,846
WE WERE FRIENDS

400
00:25:13,930 --> 00:25:18,059
To take responsibility for my actions,
I will be deleting this novel.

401
00:25:19,143 --> 00:25:21,395
If the day ever comes
when I can write again,

402
00:25:22,480 --> 00:25:23,814
I will think, reflect,

403
00:25:23,898 --> 00:25:26,025
and imagine on my own,

404
00:25:26,901 --> 00:25:29,278
so I can write something truly mine.

405
00:25:31,989 --> 00:25:33,574
Thank you for reading.

406
00:25:35,034 --> 00:25:36,244
I was so very grateful.

407
00:25:36,327 --> 00:25:38,996
HELLO, THIS IS IMUK

408
00:25:42,500 --> 00:25:44,001
Be it hate comments,

409
00:25:44,710 --> 00:25:45,670
no comments,

410
00:25:46,504 --> 00:25:48,339
my lack of skill,

411
00:25:48,422 --> 00:25:50,466
or the ridicule of those around me,

412
00:25:51,092 --> 00:25:53,928
I thought nothing could stop me
from writing.

413
00:25:55,221 --> 00:25:56,722
I believed

414
00:25:57,848 --> 00:26:00,101
I could always keep writing

415
00:26:00,726 --> 00:26:02,853
and that I always would, no matter what.

416
00:26:05,398 --> 00:26:06,816
But now,

417
00:26:08,526 --> 00:26:09,485
I can no longer…

418
00:26:09,568 --> 00:26:11,946
DO YOU WANT TO DELETE THIS NOVEL?

419
00:26:14,907 --> 00:26:16,742
…be the same as I was before.

420
00:26:16,826 --> 00:26:23,666
"WE WERE FRIENDS" HAS BEEN DELETED
RETURN TO MY TITLES

421
00:26:27,753 --> 00:26:28,713
We are gathered today

422
00:26:28,796 --> 00:26:32,049
to discuss the novel written by Yeo Eui-ju
featuring her teachers as characters.

423
00:26:32,133 --> 00:26:34,677
We won't necessarily take your side.

424
00:26:34,760 --> 00:26:37,096
I believe if Eui-ju hopes to keep writing,

425
00:26:37,179 --> 00:26:38,597
she needs to learn something from this.

426
00:26:38,681 --> 00:26:39,515
She must be expelled!

427
00:26:39,598 --> 00:26:41,058
I told her to keep writing.

428
00:26:41,142 --> 00:26:42,435
I'm the one who's responsible.

429
00:26:42,518 --> 00:26:45,271
Mr. Ga won't be able to come to school
for the time being.

430
00:26:45,354 --> 00:26:46,731
How bad is it?

431
00:26:46,814 --> 00:26:48,816
He didn't want to tell you
for fear you'd worry.

432
00:26:48,899 --> 00:26:51,360
Mr. Ga, why did you do it?

433
00:26:52,611 --> 00:26:53,696
To me, you're…

434
00:26:55,948 --> 00:26:56,949
You're…

435
00:27:55,674 --> 00:27:57,676
Subtitle: Paul Carver
